  <h2>THE WINNERS</h2>

  <p><strong>COMIC</strong></p>

  <p>Oola Dug by Malcom Sutherland</p>

  <p>Nicely drawn and put together, smartly drawn and conceived.</p>


  <p><strong>BOOK</strong></p>

  <p>Extraction! edited by Fr&eacute;d&eacute;ric Dubois, Marc Tessier and David Widgington, <a href="http://www.cumuluspress.com" title="cumulus Press">Cumulus Press</a></p>

  <p>A superb small press work, in terms of design, in terms of concept, in terms of content (both artistic and journalistic), and in terms of a truly collective effort carried out with minimal funding and time constraints.</p>


  <p><strong>ZINE</strong></p>

  <p>The Bedrooms of the Nation by Michelle Sterling</p>

  <p>The best erotic contribution to Canadiana non-fiction since Leonard Cohen&#x27;s Beautiful Losers.</p>


  <h2>THE JUDGES</h2>
  <p><strong>COMICS</strong></p>

  <p>Jamie Salomon is a long-time comics aficionado who previously published local comics under the Copacetic Comics and Crunchy Comics imprints. He is currently the controller for Drawn and Quarterly.</p>


  <p><strong>BOOKS</strong></p>

  <p>Vincent Tinguely is a Montreal writer and performance poet.</p>


  <p><strong>ZINES</strong></p>

  <p>Onya Hogan-Finlay is an artist and organizer based in Montreal. She is the co-founder of the projet MOBILIVRE-BOOKMOBILE project and a member of the Third Leg collective.</p>



